  30:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****  ===============================================================================
  31:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****                           ##### RTC Operating Condition #####
  32:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****  ===============================================================================
  33:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The real-time clock (RTC) and the RTC backup registers can be powered
  34:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        from the VBAT voltage when the main VDD supply is powered off.
  35:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        To retain the content of the RTC backup registers and supply the RTC
  36:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        when VDD is turned off, VBAT pin can be connected to an optional
  37:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        standby voltage supplied by a battery or by another source.
  38:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  39:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****                    ##### Backup Domain Reset #####
  40:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****  ===============================================================================
  41:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The backup domain reset sets all RTC registers and the RCC_BDCR register
  42:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        to their reset values.
  43:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        A backup domain reset is generated when one of the following events occurs:
  44:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) Software reset, triggered by setting the BDRST bit in the
  45:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****         RCC Backup domain control register (RCC_BDCR).
  46:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) VDD or VBAT power on, if both supplies have previously been powered off.
  47:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) Tamper detection event resets all data backup registers.
  48:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  49:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****                    ##### Backup Domain Access #####
  50:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==================================================================
  51:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] After reset, the backup domain (RTC registers and RTC backup data registers)
  52:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        is protected against possible unwanted write accesses.
  53:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] To enable access to the RTC Domain and RTC registers, proceed as follows:
  54:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Enable the Power Controller (PWR) APB1 interface clock using the
  55:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****         __HAL_RCC_PWR_CLK_ENABLE() function.
  56:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Enable access to RTC domain using the HAL_PWR_EnableBkUpAccess() function.
  57:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Select the RTC clock source using the __HAL_RCC_RTC_CONFIG() function.
  58:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Enable RTC Clock using the __HAL_RCC_RTC_ENABLE() function.
  59:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  60:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] To enable access to the RTC Domain and RTC registers, proceed as follows:
  61:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) Call the function HAL_RCCEx_PeriphCLKConfig with RCC_PERIPHCLK_RTC for
  62:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****         PeriphClockSelection and select RTCClockSelection (LSE, LSI or HSEdiv32)
  63:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) Enable RTC Clock using the __HAL_RCC_RTC_ENABLE() macro.
  64:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  65:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****                   ##### How to use RTC Driver #####
  66:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****  ===================================================================
  67:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
  68:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Enable the RTC domain access (see description in the section above).
  69:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Configure the RTC Prescaler (Asynchronous and Synchronous) and RTC hour
  70:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****         format using the HAL_RTC_Init() function.
  71:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  72:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *** Time and Date configuration ***
  73:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ===================================
  74:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
  75:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To configure the RTC Calendar (Time and Date) use the HAL_RTC_SetTime()
  76:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****         and HAL_RTC_SetDate() functions.
  77:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To read the RTC Calendar, use the HAL_RTC_GetTime() and HAL_RTC_GetDate() functions.
  78:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  79:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *** Alarm configuration ***
  80:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ===========================
  81:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
  82:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To configure the RTC Alarm use the HAL_RTC_SetAlarm() function.
  83:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****             You can also configure the RTC Alarm with interrupt mode using the
  84:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****             HAL_RTC_SetAlarm_IT() function.
  85:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To read the RTC Alarm, use the HAL_RTC_GetAlarm() function.
  86:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\solar\AppData\Local\Temp\ccoZwvur.s 			page 3


  87:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****                   ##### RTC and low power modes #####
  88:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==================================================================
  89:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The MCU can be woken up from a low power mode by an RTC alternate
  90:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        function.
  91:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The RTC alternate functions are the RTC alarms (Alarm A and Alarm B),
  92:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        RTC wakeup, RTC tamper event detection and RTC time stamp event detection.
  93:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        These RTC alternate functions can wake up the system from the Stop and
  94:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        Standby low power modes.
  95:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The system can also wake up from low power modes without depending
  96:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        on an external interrupt (Auto-wakeup mode), by using the RTC alarm
  97:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        or the RTC wakeup events.
  98:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The RTC provides a programmable time base for waking up from the
  99:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        Stop or Standby mode at regular intervals.
 100:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        Wakeup from STOP and STANDBY modes is possible only when the RTC clock source
 101:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****        is LSE or LSI.
 102:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 103:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *** Callback registration ***
 104:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   =============================================
 105:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 106:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 107:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   When The compilation define USE_HAL_RTC_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 108:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   not defined, the callback registration feature is not available and all callbacks
 109:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   are set to the corresponding weak functions. This is the recommended configuration
 110:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   in order to optimize memory/code consumption footprint/performances.
 111:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 112:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 113:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   The compilation define  USE_RTC_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
 114:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 115:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Use Function HAL_RTC_RegisterCallback() to register an interrupt callback.
 116:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 117:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 118:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Function HAL_RTC_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
 119:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) AlarmAEventCallback          : RTC Alarm A Event callback.
 120:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) AlarmBEventCallback          : RTC Alarm B Event callback.
 121:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) TimeStampEventCallback       : RTC TimeStamp Event callback.
 122:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) WakeUpTimerEventCallback     : RTC WakeUpTimer Event callback.
 123:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** #if defined (STM32L4P5xx) || defined (STM32L4Q5xx)
 124:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) SSRUEventCallback            : RTC SSRU Event callback.
 125:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** #endif
 126:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper1EventCallback         : RTC Tamper 1 Event callback.
 127:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper2EventCallback         : RTC Tamper 2 Event callback.
 128:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper3EventCallback         : RTC Tamper 3 Event callback.
 129:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback              : RTC MspInit callback.
 130:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback            : RTC MspDeInit callback.
 131:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 132:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   and a pointer to the user callback function.
 133:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 134:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 135:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Use function HAL_RTC_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 136:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   weak function.
 137:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   HAL_RTC_UnRegisterCallback() takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 138:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   and the Callback ID.
 139:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   This function allows to reset following callbacks:
 140:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) AlarmAEventCallback          : RTC Alarm A Event callback.
 141:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) AlarmBEventCallback          : RTC Alarm B Event callback.
 142:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) TimeStampEventCallback       : RTC TimeStamp Event callback.
 143:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) WakeUpTimerEventCallback     : RTC WakeUpTimer Event callback.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\solar\AppData\Local\Temp\ccoZwvur.s 			page 4


 144:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** #if defined (STM32L4P5xx) || defined (STM32L4Q5xx)
 145:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) SSRUEventCallback            : RTC SSRU Event callback.
 146:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** #endif
 147:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper1EventCallback         : RTC Tamper 1 Event callback.
 148:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper2EventCallback         : RTC Tamper 2 Event callback.
 149:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper3EventCallback         : RTC Tamper 3 Event callback.
 150:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback              : RTC MspInit callback.
 151:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback            : RTC MspDeInit callback.
 152:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 153:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 154:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   By default, after the HAL_RTC_Init() and when the state is HAL_RTC_STATE_RESET,
 155:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions :
 156:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   examples AlarmAEventCallback(), TimeStampEventCallback().
 157:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit callbacks that are reset to the legacy weak function
 158:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   in the HAL_RTC_Init()/HAL_RTC_DeInit() only when these callbacks are null
 159:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   (not registered beforehand).
 160:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, HAL_RTC_Init()/HAL_RTC_DeInit()
 161:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand)
 162:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 163:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 164:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_RTC_STATE_READY state only.
 165:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit that can be registered/unregistered
 166:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   in HAL_RTC_STATE_READY or HAL_RTC_STATE_RESET state,
 167:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 168:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 169:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   using HAL_RTC_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_RTC_DeInit()
 170:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   or HAL_RTC_Init() function.
