2498:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   * @brief  Wait until the RTC Time and Date registers (RTC_TR and RTC_DR) are
2499:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         synchronized with RTC APB clock.
2500:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   * @note   The RTC Resynchronization mode is write protected, use the
2501:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         __HAL_RTC_WRITEPROTECTION_DISABLE() before calling this function.
2502:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   * @note   To read the calendar through the shadow registers after Calendar
2503:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         initialization, calendar update or after wakeup from low power modes
2504:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         the software must first clear the RSF flag.
2505:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         The software must then wait until it is set again before reading
2506:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         the calendar, which means that the calendar registers have been
2507:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   *         correctly copied into the RTC_TR and RTC_DR shadow registers.
2508:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   * @param  hrtc RTC handle
2509:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   * @retval HAL status
2510:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc.c ****   */
